>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.canadiancommentary.com/everquest/images/background.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/beverquestersofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=galadriaculravenni>Galadria Culravenni</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 329<br> <font color=#8B4513>(6/17/01 2:10:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Heroism in Qeynos Aqueducts</span><hr size=1> Last night Galladen, one of our less experienced members, somehow got into the Qeynos Aqueducts and got himself killed there. Ordained went to try to help him, but unfortunately ran into a blue undead of some sort who aggroed and harm-touched him for half his life before he even knew what hit him, and he died as well... The whole thing turned into one of those hours long nightmares, I understand, and finally Ordained camped to come back with another character he thought might have a better chance at success. He had barely arrived at the Qeynos docks when I got a tell from one Cadip, a level 15 human cleric of the guild Ordo Ursi Prismatus. <br>
<br>
Evidently Cadip had felt so badly earlier at being too low to help Ordained that he spoke to one of his guildmates who has seriously considered leaving EQ for good - a level 49 cleric named Rugen Payne. Rugen, in spite of his disenchantment with the game, went to great lengths to locate Galladen's corpse and painstakingly drag it along the tunnels and to safety. By the time he had accomplished this, Galladen had logged off for the night, which is rather too bad, but Cadip and Rugen took the time and the concern to contact me and let me know where the corpse was left so that Gall might later retrieve it!<br>
<br>
Rugen told me he had died twice at the same spot Ordained died, whether that night or earlier he did not specify. After rescuing Galladen's corpse, Rugen responded to still another plea for help to retrieve a corpse in the Aqueduct and re-entered, dying yet a third time. Alas, seems that is one nasty hole to attempt!<br>
<br>
I cannot praise Rugen enough for the sacrifice he made for a Victus Fortis member, or he and Cadip enough for their courtesy in conveying the information to another Victus Fortis member (myself) in the absence of the player concerned, once the rescue had been completed. This goes WAY beyond kindness.<br>
<br>
Galadria<br>
&quot;My joy is in Victus Fortis&quot;<br>
<br>
Kemie<br>
&quot;My joy is in giving&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/uraloth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raloth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 613<br> <font color=#8B4513>(6/17/01 3:40:14 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.canadiancommentary.com/head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Heroism in Qeynos Aqueducts</span><hr size=1> Wow!  That is a noble man indeed!  Dying so many times at that level to help others is an unshelfish loss of that hard-to-earn exp!!!<br>
<br>
/em bows to the kind Rugen<br>
<br>
<br>
Take care,<br>
<br>
Raloth<br>
