<br>
And Galladen, you have to start adventuring without your gear on so when you die in these impossible places you don't have to take up the time and lives of so many other people getting you out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   At your level you won't lose any (or little) xp, so you will have nothing to lose. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/ugladriellumenaura.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gladriel Lumenaura</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#8B4513>(6/18/01 12:15:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Heroism in Qeynos Aqueducts</span><hr size=1> Exceptional people, both of the clerics - and Ordained no less so for having the added motivation of helping out a guildmate. We've all been in situations that seem beyond our abilities to put right, but just as we can't depend on a kind stranger to walk by, we should not presume on the assistance of our few higher level members to help us out when the water gets too hot or too deep.<br>
<br>
Kind gentlemen indeed - I wonder if there's something about the cleric class that attracts these exceptional people? Oh, and druids too of course...rangers too...and as for the monks - wow...palladins? what can I say....incredible.<br>
<br>
Gladriel Lumenaura <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/beverquestersofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=galadriaculravenni>Galadria Culravenni</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 331<br> <font color=#8B4513>(6/18/01 9:03:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Heroism in Qeynos Aqueducts</span><hr size=1> Hehe... fools rush in, they say. I understand from chatting last night to one of our guildmates that Galladen was advised not to go in there in the first place! I admit I was in the middle of other things (like fighting) when any earlier conversation was going on and evidently missed that part, as did Ordained.<br>
<br>
My friends, ALWAYS listen to your guildmates' advice! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    A level six character has plenty of &quot;newbie&quot; areas to fight in without having to venture into tougher zones... unless you have a higher level player along with you who is helping to power level you or something!<br>
<br>
Because yes, we can't always count on the kindness of strangers nor should we expect our own higher level players to come and sacrifice their levels just to help you out of a bind you shouldn't have gotten into in the first place. Most of us don't mind helping others - in fact, that's one of the nice things about many of the members of VF - they like helping out. But speaking from my own experiences, I know that I find myself less and less willing to help out a particular individual who makes repeated errors in judgement first, and then just takes the help for granted instead of appreciating what is sometimes a great sacrifice (and not much fun) on my part... <br>
<br>
Think before you leap into the frying pan - accidents happen and I never mind helping in that case, particularly if it is within my capabilities as a player or those of my character, and in fact it often gives me great pleasure. I'm sure others feel the same way. But with players who help me - and in fact with GM's as well (and I think in general they probably respond EXACTLY the same way as I do to helping people) - I always bend over backwards to show my gratitude and appreciation...<br>
<br>
Galadria<br>
&quot;My joy is in Victus Fortis&quot;<br>
<br>
Kemie<br>
&quot;My joy is in giving&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm18.showMessage?topicID=35.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm18.showMessage?topicID=33.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm18.emailToFriend?topicID=36.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm18.threadControl?topicID=36.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm18.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=36.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm18.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=36.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub44.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm20">General Forum<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm16">Gatherings of the Brave<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm25">Bazaar of the Brave<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm17">Tales and Roleplay<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm15">Questing<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm18">Honour Role <option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm19">Dishonourable Denizens<option val